    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "Node 1: Sanitize & Clean Data (Code Node)\nReal world data from Google Sheets is rarely\nperfect. This node cleans the incoming data by:\n- Replacing empty/null values with 0\n- Converting text numbers to actual numbers\n- Flagging the data as sanitized\nWithout this step, empty cells would cause the\nentire workflow to crash or produce incorrect\nreports!\n\nNode 2: Validate Required Fields (IF Node)\nAfter cleaning, this node checks if the date\nfield exists and is valid. If the date is\nmissing or unknown, the report cannot be\naccurately generated. Invalid data is\nimmediately flagged and the admin team gets\nnotified via Slack before any further\nprocessing occurs.\n\nTogether these two nodes ensure that only\nclean, valid and reliable data reaches the\nreport generation stage! 💡"
      },
